title: High Child Employment in Agriculture
description: In 2015, 94.65% of economically active children aged 7-14 in Gambia were employed in agriculture, one of the highest rates globally.

title: Low Food Production Index
description: Gambia's food production index was 71.08 in 2022, indicating one of the lowest levels of food production compared to the 2014-2016 baseline.

title: High Merchandise Exports Outside Region
description: In 2023, 97.38% of Gambia's merchandise exports were to low- and middle-income economies outside its region, showcasing a strong export focus.

title: Low Communication and Computer Service Exports
description: In 2023, only 1.12% of Gambia's service exports were from communications and computer services, one of the lowest proportions globally.
